claim.claim-text:
1. A method for forming a structure, the method comprising:
forming a first strained semiconductor layer over a first substrate to define a layer structure, the layer structure comprising a porous layer defining a cleave plane;
forming a first relaxed layer over the first substrate;
planarizing the first relaxed layer;
forming a second relaxed layer over the first relaxed layer after the first relaxed layer is planarized;
bonding the first strained semiconductor layer to an insulator layer disposed on a second substrate; and
removing the first substrate from the first strained semiconductor layer by cleaving at the cleave plane, the strained semiconductor layer remaining bonded to the insulator layer,
wherein the first relaxed layer includes the porous layer defining a cleave plane; and the first strained semiconductor layer is formed over the first and second relaxed layers.

5. A method for forming a structure, the method comprising:
forming a first relaxed layer over a first substrate;
thereafter forming a porous layer by forming a plurality of pores in the first relaxed layer to define a cleave plane;
forming a first strained semiconductor layer over the first substrate and the first relaxed layer to define a layer structure;
bonding the first strained semiconductor layer to an insulator layer disposed on a second substrate; and
removing the first substrate from the first strained semiconductor layer by cleaving at the cleave plane, the strained semiconductor layer remaining bonded to the insulator layer.
